# Cloudflare Pages security headers for the SvelteKit frontend (public DMZ layer).
#
# NOTE: the Content-Security-Policy is intentionally NOT set here. SvelteKit emits a
# stronger, per-request nonce-based CSP for every HTML response (see kit.csp in
# svelte.config.js). Adding a second, static CSP header would be intersected with it and
# would block SvelteKit's nonced inline scripts. These headers cover everything else.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
